Simulate doublets

SimulateDoublets.Rd

Simulates doublets by summing pairs of randomly selected cells from a matrix.

Usage

SimulateDoublets(
  count_data,
  ref_cells1 = NULL,
  ref_cells2 = NULL,
  n_sim = 1000,
  seed = 37,
  method = c("average", "sum"),
  simulated_cell_prefix = "simcell_",
  return_id = FALSE,
  verbose = TRUE
)

Arguments

count_data

A count matrix. Rows are features, and columns are cells.

ref_cells1, ref_cells2

A character vector with cell names or indices to use as the first and second reference populations. If NULL, all cells are used.

n_sim

An integer with the number of doublets to simulate.

seed

An integer with the seed for the random number generator.

method

A character with the method to use to simulate doublets. Options are "average" (average of the two cells) or "sum" (sum of the two cells).

simulated_cell_prefix

A character with the prefix to use for the simulated doublet cell names.

return_id

If TRUE, returns a list with the simulated doublet counts and a tibble withe their original cell IDs. If FALSE, returns only the simulated doublet counts.

verbose

Print messages.

Value

A matrix with simulated doublets. Rows are features, and columns are simulated doublets.

Examples

dat <- matrix(rnorm(1000), ncol = 10)
SimulateDoublets(dat, n_sim = 1000)
